@postfightBOOKS If I brought them back to life by doing this I am truly sorry. If I prevented this from happening to you consider us even.
@postfightBOOKS Nonetheless I hope this helps you.
@postfightBOOKS If things were perfect I may have been your best friend but sadly I am a memory in a book - that you may not even read.
@postfightBOOKS My thoughts and experiences can't be deciphered now because they were not meant for now. I was not meant for now.
@postfightBOOKS This may be foreign to you like some hieroglyphs on a pyramid but I have to try.
@postfightBOOKS Or maybe in your time there will no longer be pain.
@postfightBOOKS - you keep me company. I write through this pain to take away from some that you may experience.

@postfightBOOKS To be strong enough to realize that you create them -- to be strong enough to realize that they may create you.
@postfightBOOKS These quotes engrained in the minds of the youth. To be aware of these monsters that haunt you no matter where you go.
@postfightBOOKS -- figures of the past trying to force their way into the present. In the end they will end up in the future.
@postfightBOOKS My eyes will burn from the sight behind my eyelids eyelids
@postfightBOOKS My dreams will whisper secrets I will forget when I rub my eyes in the morning.
@postfightBOOKS When my hand cramps up and the pen dries up, my mind will continue to make sense of this all.
@postfightBOOKS Part 2: When everything is all said and done -- I will still have much more to write.
@postfightBOOKS -- I did everything you could have wanted and I did everything you could never imagine.
@postfightBOOKS I was your biggest excuse and I was your biggest accomplishment
@postfightBOOKS They were wrong about me. Yes I couldn't save you all but I was never meant to.
@postfightBOOKS Became smart enough to put myself together and through that became self aware. Made a ruined path into one worth walking on.
@postfightBOOKS -- and I was told that I failed. They tried to break me and they did so many times.
@postfightBOOKS I was raised to carry their regrets. I came into the world in hopes of bringing together two broken people together
@postfightBOOKS When I realized what I was truly dealing with, the blindfolds placed on me as a child, I became truly aware of who I was.
@postfightBOOKS This mixture created confusion within me. Am I strong for enduring or a weak fool for letting it last this long?
@postfightBOOKS For too long I held the weight they threw on me. I grew strong but broken maintaining it all.
@postfightBOOKS When I began to realize that the failures of others resulted in my misfortune, then and only then I took my first breath.
Part 1: They blamed me for ruining our lives and they blamed me for why they couldn't put it back together.

@postfightBOOKS  Mind swollen &filled with the abuse of the years that tortured it.
@postfightBOOKS Are you really ready to see what you have done to your mind?
@postfightBOOKS  Still will lead you to your burial -- maintain your focus and discover who you really are.
@postfightBOOKS -pull the weeds out, reach through the tangled vines, dirty your hands with the dark soil but be careful not to stay still.

@postfightBOOKS grow more pride and ignore the people whose only goal is to try to fix you enough to use you.
@postfightBOOKS Be more than just the damaged goods you believed yourself to be. Be more than just the item people walk past &feel bad for
@postfightBOOKS Grow into the man you thought you could be instead of the man they tried to force you to be.
@postfightBOOKS  I indulged in self harm mentally for so long that I don't know whether next year things will grow.
@postfightBOOKS From sleeping with the enemy to believing they were family --
@postfightBOOKS Family is such a strong word but the word enemy sums up how strong these thoughts stem from.
@postfightBOOKS Nine times I moved from closet to one room studios that made me feel a false sense of closeness with my family.
@postfightBOOKS -- which shot in my fists ready to be the man of the house at nine.
@postfightBOOKS -- the look they gave my little sister gave me chills up my spine
@postfightBOOKS Buildings I wished I could live in while we walked past the homeless drunken men
@postfightBOOKS Mind that grows too many things at once, and watches them tangle into vines left on old abandoned buildings.
@postfightBOOKS Nightmares that sprout out of the dark soil that is my mind.
